Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.01,0:00:06.13,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemy is a science where one understands the structure of matter, breaks it down, then rebuilds it.  
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.13,0:00:11.74,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, it is not an all-powerful technique,\Nas one cannot create something out of nothing.  
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.55,0:00:17.88,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,If one wishes to gain something,\None must present something of equal value.  
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.88,0:00:22.29,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,This is the concept of equivalent exchange, the fundamental basis of alchemy.  
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.96,0:00:26.95,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is a taboo in alchemy. Human transmutation.  
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.95,0:00:29.78,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,One must not commit this act.  
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.76,0:02:05.39,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Scar, a man who only targets State Alchemists, 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.39,0:02:07.65,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,attacked Edward Elric. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.27,0:02:12.46,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Although Ed accepted death at Scar's hand, 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.46,0:02:16.65,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,his life was saved thanks to interference by Colonel Mustang and his men. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.58,0:02:21.79,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Ed and Al, who discovered the joy of being alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.79,0:02:28.50,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,decided to return to their birthplace, Resembool, to restore their bodies. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.82,0:02:38.59,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Yo. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.03,0:02:41.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel Hughes. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.85,0:02:45.34,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,The guys at Eastern Headquarters said that they were too busy to come. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.34,0:02:47.02,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm here to see you off instead. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.02,0:02:48.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine with me, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.25,0:02:51.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...why is the Major... 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.05,0:02:52.49,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural you'd get an escort. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.49,0:02:56.48,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Getting attacked by Scar in your state wouldn't be too pretty, would it? 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.24,0:03:01.16,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Just accept the Major's kindness. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.69,0:03:03.63,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Children don't need to be reserved. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.63,0:03:05.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't treat me like a kid!  
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.82,0:03:08.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And Al is going to be on this ride, too, right? 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.75,0:03:09.54,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.50,0:03:17.31,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he'd be lonely riding alone. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.30,0:03:18.55,Default-alt,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell do you take my brother for?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.80,0:03:21.34,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's time. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.38,0:03:26.58,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Well guys, take care. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.58,0:03:29.28,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever happen to stop by Central again, come say hi. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.54,0:04:06.30,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Marcoh! 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.30,0:04:08.83,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,You're Dr. Marcoh, aren't you?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.24,0:04:12.79,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Alex Louis Armstrong from Central! 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.59,0:04:16.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Someone you know? 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.82,0:04:19.75,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,He's a talented alchemist who used to reside in Central. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.66,0:04:24.30,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,He was studying how to apply alchemy to medical treatment,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.30,0:04:27.91,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,but he had been reported missing after the civil war in Ishbal. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.36,0:04:30.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get off here, Major. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.48,0:04:35.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I have a feeling he'd know something about the transmutation of living organisms. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.33,0:04:43.40,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know someone who looks like this? 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.40,0:04:45.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you're good at drawing. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.61,0:04:49.77,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Drawing portraits is a skill that has been passed down in the Armstrong household for generations. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.77,0:04:52.17,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,This is Dr. Mauro, isn't it? 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.17,0:04:52.77,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,"Mauro"? 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.10,0:04:57.19,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,We were in a tight spot because our doctors were drafted for the civil war. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.57,0:05:00.52,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what would have happened if Dr. Mauro hadn't come. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.99,0:05:05.03,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't abandon a single patient\Nno matter who it is. We owe him so much. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.03,0:05:08.53,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,It's like something flashes before your eyes,\Nand suddenly, your wounds are already healed. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:12.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This must be the place. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.31,0:05:17.00,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.00,0:05:18.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.85,0:05:20.22,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you come here? 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.22,0:05:22.12,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Are you here to take me back?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.49,0:05:24.46,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Please calm down, Doctor. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.46,0:05:26.66,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to go back there anymore. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.66,0:05:27.72,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Please, let me go! 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.72,0:05:29.09,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,No, you've got it all wrong! We just... 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.31,0:05:31.18,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Then did you come here to seal my mouth?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.18,0:05:32.51,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,No, we... 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.51,0:05:34.19,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You can't trick me! 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.61,0:05:39.53,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you to please calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.53,0:05:40.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al!!! 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:48.70,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea you were hiding out in the countryside under an assumed name. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.41,0:05:54.37,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I heard a rumor you took some classified documents with you when you disappeared. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.13,0:05:56.94,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't stand it any longer. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.73,0:05:59.61,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, it was an order from the superiors... 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.98,0:06:02.84,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,...but because of it, I had to stain my hands by conducting research on such a thing... 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.84,0:06:04.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Such a thing"? 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.18,0:06:11.09,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,So many innocent people died because of it in the civil war in Ishbal... 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.95,0:06:17.60,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I can't atone for what I've done, even with my life. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.19,0:06:23.23,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,So I decided to become a doctor for this town because I wanted to do all I could to pay for my sins. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.00,0:06:29.99,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor, what exactly were you ordered to research? 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.48,0:06:32.74,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,The Philosopher's Stone. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.93,0:06:41.16,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,The things I took with me are\Nthe research data and the stone itself. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.16,0:06:43.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You have the stone?! Here?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.18,0:06:55.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that a liquid, not a stone? 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.08,0:07:02.67,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,"The Philosopher's Stone"... 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.67,0:07:04.16,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,"The Heavenly Stone"... 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.73,0:07:08.01,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,"The Great Elixir"... "The Red Tincture"... 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.01,0:07:09.44,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,"The Fifth Element". 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.93,0:07:17.20,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't necessarily in the shape of a stone,\Njust as how the stone itself has many different names. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.98,0:07:20.13,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,But this is incomplete. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.13,0:07:24.04,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know when it'll reach its limit and become unusable. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.30,0:07:29.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But it definitely displayed its power during the Ishbalan war. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.18,0:07:31.97,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Same with the bogus High Priest of Lior. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.54,0:07:37.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,His abilities were improved,\Neven though the stone was incomplete. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.91,0:07:44.48,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If something like that can be made,\Nit's possible to perfect it if we give it more research! 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.02,0:07:49.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Marcoh, please show me the research data! 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.50,0:07:52.99,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Major... who is this boy? 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.45,0:07:55.91,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,He's a State Alchemist. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.13,0:07:59.79,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,A boy like this... 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.09,0:08:06.27,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,There were so many alchemists who gave up their state qualifications after the civil war... 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.27,0:08:10.11,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,...because they couldn't stand being human weapons... 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.51,0:08:11.91,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, you... 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.91,0:08:14.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's stupid! 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.22,0:08:21.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm willing to go through hell until I achieve my goal! 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.16,0:08:30.90,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I see... so you broke the taboo... 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.18,0:08:34.50,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.50,0:08:38.33,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You were able to affix the soul of a human being. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.33,0:08:43.51,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You just might be able to create a perfect Philosopher's Stone. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.51,0:08:44.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then... 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.70,0:08:46.42,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I can't show you the data. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.42,0:08:47.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But! 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.02,0:08:49.93,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't desire such a thing. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.93,0:08:51.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's to get our bodies back?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.40,0:08:52.92,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't! 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.51,0:08:55.33,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,That is the Devil's research. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.33,0:08:57.46,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You'll see Hell if you study it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.39,0:09:00.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen Hell already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.68,0:09:05.19,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Please, leave... 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.11,0:09:21.48,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen Hell already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.80,0:09:28.42,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really okay? 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.85,0:09:35.10,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,It's incomplete, but we could have taken at least the stone by force. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.10,0:09:39.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I wanted it. I wanted it so badly, but... 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.21,0:09:46.15,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We don't want to steal the only support the people in this town have in order to get our bodies back. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.32,0:09:51.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's good enough that we found out\Na Philosopher's Stone can be created. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.53,0:09:53.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We'll look for another way. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.53,0:09:57.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But what about you, though? 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.85,0:10:01.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have to report Dr. Marcoh to Central? 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.27,0:10:06.94,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,The person I met today is\Na town doctor by the name of Mauro. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.95,0:10:09.87,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.27,0:10:16.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Marcoh. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.48,0:10:19.74,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,This is where the data is hidden. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.55,0:10:24.47,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,If you still feel you won't regret\Ndiscovering the truth, take a look. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.08,0:10:29.73,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You may be able to reach\Nthe real truth that is beyond truth... 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.45,0:10:33.03,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,No... this is unnecessary. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.48,0:10:38.89,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I pray you boys will be able to get your bodies back. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.33,0:10:47.43,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What does it say, Brother? 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:51.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,National Central Library, 1st Branch. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.03,0:10:55.30,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Makes sense. A forest would be\Nan ideal place to hide a tree, after all. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.76,0:10:58.93,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,There are enough books in there to last several lifetimes. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.97,0:11:03.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can find a clue to getting the stone here. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.61,0:11:12.81,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,There you are, Marcoh. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.20,0:11:30.12,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Winry! Winry! 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.91,0:11:32.65,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,You've got an old customer at the door! 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.63,0:11:36.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Granny. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.24,0:11:37.28,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We're back! 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.28,0:11:39.30,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,God, what happened to you two? 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.30,0:11:42.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A lot. We're going to need your help again. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.35,0:11:46.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This is Major Armstrong. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.71,0:11:48.43,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Pleasure to meet you, I'm Pinako Rockbell. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.58,0:11:54.32,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,But gosh darn, looks like Ed got shorter after not seeing him for some time. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.47,0:12:00.19,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I'm pretty sure you're supposed to say "got taller" at times like this... 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.65,0:12:02.95,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,If you really did, then I'd say so. 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.95,0:12:04.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say, you minimum hag?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.87,0:12:11.82,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you to give me a call\Nbefore stopping by for maintenance?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.82,0:12:13.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You trying to kill me, Winry?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.28,0:12:18.59,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back! 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.80,0:12:19.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.42,0:12:25.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,My bad, my bad. It broke. 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.74,0:12:27.38,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,"Broke"? 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.38,0:12:31.34,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,An automail of the highest quality... That I worked so hard on... 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.34,0:12:33.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, to smithereens. 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.58,0:12:38.34,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,And Al is broken, too? 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.86,0:12:41.49,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck have you guys been doing? 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.53,0:12:47.08,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,All you ever do is worry me! 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.68,0:12:49.74,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,I see. 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.65,0:12:56.53,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,So you want to return to Central as soon as possible to get that data, eh? 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.53,0:12:59.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. So I want you to fix me up as quick as you can. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.54,0:13:03.89,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I'll need to adjust your leg,\Ntoo, and not just your arm. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.89,0:13:06.81,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, seems like you've at least grown a bit. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.81,0:13:07.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.21,0:13:11.93,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike your leg though, I'm going to have to remake your arm from scratch. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.49,0:13:14.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Will it take a week? 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.53,0:13:16.19,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate me. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.57,0:13:19.44,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Three days. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.99,0:13:23.62,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to bear with a spare for now. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.62,0:13:24.48,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.96,0:13:28.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's tough to walk when you're not used to the leg. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.95,0:13:31.08,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fix it up before you get used to it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.31,0:13:32.56,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But seriously... 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.56,0:13:35.59,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Materials... Assembly... Connection... Calibration...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.05,0:13:37.76,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be all-nighters, no doubt. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.76,0:13:39.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for being so unreasonable. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.58,0:13:42.80,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,But you want to go back to Central as soon as possible, right? 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.12,0:13:45.09,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll work to make that happen! 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.09,0:13:48.79,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,But we'll charge extra for the express fee! 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.12,0:14:00.56,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,It's finished. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.56,0:14:02.29,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.03,0:14:06.35,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see Edward Elric around. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.35,0:14:10.14,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he said that he was visiting his mother's grave. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.25,0:14:19.11,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Major. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.66,0:14:23.40,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of lives have those boys been living? 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.24,0:14:27.63,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They don't even send us a single letter. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.32,0:14:33.06,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,They are famous alchemists, even in Central. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.06,0:14:36.85,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,That drags them into trouble, as well... 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.39,0:14:41.15,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,But don't worry. Those boys are strong. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.90,0:14:43.24,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Are they? 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.19,0:14:45.88,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,That makes me feel better, at least. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.37,0:14:52.68,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Are those two like grandchildren to you? 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.13,0:14:56.12,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,I've been watching over them ever since they were born. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.07,0:15:01.50,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Their father was an old drinking buddy of mine, 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:05.92,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,but he left the village, leaving his wife and children behind. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.57,0:15:09.16,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even know if he's still alive. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.79,0:15:21.98,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think about it, where are Miss Winry's parents? 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.42,0:15:23.58,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They died. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.58,0:15:25.48,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,During the Ishbalan war. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.59,0:15:31.78,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,My son... her parents... were surgeons. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.62,0:15:35.99,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They left for the battlefield because there was a shortage of doctors, but... 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.46,0:15:39.00,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,It was a horrible war. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.98,0:15:41.29,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,It sure was. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.83,0:15:46.78,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shucks. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.78,0:15:49.32,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,It's about time to start preparing supper. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.68,0:15:52.73,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,You look like you'd eat a lot,\Nso you can expect a big dinner. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.73,0:15:56.02,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no, I can't trouble you any further... 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.56,0:15:59.24,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,A meal tastes better with more people at the table. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.24,0:16:02.44,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,There's an extra bed open for patients, so you can sleep there. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.41,0:16:06.80,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only place those brothers can stay, anyway. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.20,0:16:09.44,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Adding an extra guest won't make a difference. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.24,0:16:11.82,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,What about their home? 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.44,0:16:16.45,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,It's gone. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.15,0:16:19.14,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They don't have a home to return to. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.39,0:16:26.30,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They burnt their house down the day Ed decided to leave this village after getting his state qualification. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.42,0:16:33.09,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They probably did it to make sure there would be no going back. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.53,0:16:40.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.08,0:16:43.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,They're all waiting for us. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.78,0:16:48.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're ba- 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.55,0:16:50.07,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Edward Elric! 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.46,0:16:56.08,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Your innocent love that drove you to attempt to revive your mother! 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.08,0:17:01.64,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Your tremendous love that drove you to affix your brother's soul while prepared to throw your own life away! 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.64,0:17:07.26,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx97}Your unearthly determination that drove you to destroy your way out by burning down your home filled with memories! 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.26,0:17:11.17,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Accept my embrace!!! 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.17,0:17:14.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Get away! It's too hot! 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.09,0:17:15.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!!! 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.55,0:17:37.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you guys are at it already! So early in the morning, too! 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.66,0:17:38.76,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,We've been working all night. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.58,0:17:47.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, it's so late and you guys are still working! 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.70,0:17:49.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be done pretty soon at this rate, won't ya?! 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.40,0:17:50.85,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Another all-nighter tonight. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.31,0:17:52.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wha... 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.10,0:18:04.93,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Out! 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.59,0:18:13.69,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,They said they'd get it done in three days, so wait patiently. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.69,0:18:21.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know, but I just can't sit still when I know a secret to the Philosopher's Stone lies in Central! 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.60,0:18:27.54,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the wait! We're done! 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.25,0:18:31.27,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,You up for this? 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.27,0:18:32.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.54,0:18:33.21,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Ready... 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.39,0:18:34.13,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Set... 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.28,0:18:34.89,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Go! 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.19,0:18:41.55,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This feeling of connecting my nerves gets me every time. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.55,0:18:46.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I won't have to deal with this pain once I get the Philosopher's Stone! 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.56,0:18:49.73,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,That's too bad. You were a real money-spinner. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.60,0:18:54.19,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There's no need to go through the trouble of getting your limbs back! 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.27,0:18:57.01,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, what's wrong with this? 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.01,0:18:59.70,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,The smell of oil, the groaning of bearings... 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.70,0:19:04.56,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,This beautiful form that was designed based on human engineering! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.56,0:19:06.79,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, how amazing! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.02,0:19:08.32,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Automails, that is! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.32,0:19:09.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Machine freak. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.66,0:19:11.79,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, Alchemy freak. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.53,0:19:14.34,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,All right, it's complete! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.27,0:19:18.09,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,How is it? 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.33,0:19:20.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Feels great! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.22,0:19:24.14,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,We raised the ratio of chromium this time so it would be more resistant to rust. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.43,0:19:27.97,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But that makes it less durable, so don't overuse- 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.18,0:19:29.47,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, listen to me! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.01,0:19:30.56,Default-alt,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al, sorry for the wait! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.96,0:19:33.56,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be able to fix him quickly? 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:36.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There's a trick to it, though. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.14,0:19:43.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This seal right here acts as the mediator between Al's soul and this suit, 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.20,0:19:45.49,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,so I have to make sure I don't mess it up. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.79,0:19:53.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,There! Perfect! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.39,0:19:55.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say we test it out! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.22,0:19:56.71,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Sure! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.33,0:20:02.09,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,It'll get quiet around here. 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.01,0:20:05.01,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally time! 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.01,0:20:08.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to go find Dr. Marcoh's data at Central! 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.19,0:20:11.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving on the first train tomorrow! 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.56,0:20:25.87,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,He's sleeping with his belly out, again. 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.87,0:20:27.33,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously... 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.71,0:20:29.80,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You're like his guardian, Al. 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.29,0:20:32.87,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pain having such a needy brother. 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.20,0:20:36.08,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,How old are you boys now? 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.71,0:20:39.38,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fourteen, and Brother is fifteen. 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.61,0:20:47.97,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,He's so short, the same age as me,\Nand they call him a human weapon? 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.87,0:20:50.57,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Look how defenseless he is right now. 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.35,0:20:53.01,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks a lot, you two. 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.25,0:20:56.36,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What's this formality all of a sudden? 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.81,0:21:02.57,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You've always welcomed us as family. I'm really thankful of you two. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.39,0:21:07.02,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,He might not say it, but Brother feels the same way. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.82,0:21:08.60,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al... 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.42,0:21:11.75,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, we know. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.20,0:21:14.47,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to say it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.92,0:21:17.33,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Granny... Winry... 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.17,0:21:19.29,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.36,0:21:25.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for everything, Granny. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.26,0:21:26.09,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.09,0:21:28.29,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Winry? 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.29,0:21:30.52,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Her last few nights have all been all-nighters, so I bet she's exhausted. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.52,0:21:31.99,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Want me to go wake her up? 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.99,0:21:33.84,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, don't worry about it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.84,0:21:36.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,She'll just keep on ranting about maintenance and all that stuff. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.89,0:21:37.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Later. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.83,0:21:40.68,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you two. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.01,0:21:44.53,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Stop by for a meal every once in a while, will ya? 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.53,0:21:45.74,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We will. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.01,0:21:49.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Coming to a place so deep in the mountains just for a meal? 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.77,0:21:53.54,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Ed, Al. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.48,0:21:55.79,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Have a safe trip... 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.79,0:22:00.68,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yup! 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.45,0:23:44.36,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I slept for the whole day. 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.40,0:23:48.73,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously... this place turns into a battlefield whenever he comes. 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.32,0:23:52.97,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.71,0:23:56.74,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops? 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.12,0:24:02.13,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Clues to the Philosopher's Stone are certainly there. 
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.13,0:24:06.35,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, the enemy's evil hand has seized its target,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.35,0:24:13.65,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,and the boys are drawn into a labyrinth by the real truth that is beyond the truth. 
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.65,0:24:17.81,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist: 
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.81,0:24:20.81,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 7, The Hidden Truth. 
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.78,0:24:25.42,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,If you wish to reach it, you must not avert your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.42,0:24:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
